And for the same reason, slaves and other property are not restored at peace, except by com- pact3 for they are supposed to be taken by right, and to deny this, would be to make wars grow out of wars. Whence it appears that what is alleged by Quintilian for the Thebans, is ingenious, but not true.

V. A free man returns by postliminium, if he comes to his own party with this intent: inasmuch as, in order that a slave [or a captive] may become free he must, 50 to speak, acquire himself, which cannot be done without his will.
